The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Sourav sees role model in Anand
                                                   Sourav sees role model in Anand
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Indias most successful cricket captain Sourav Ganguly was all praises for Viswanathan Anand and said that the world chess champion has been an inspiration for all, including the Indian cricket team.         
	Speaking at a felicitation , Anand and Olympic gold medallist Abhinav Bindra, the southpaw said: Anand is a role model for everyone I have been following him for years Its not just me, he has inspired the entire Indian cricket team.         
	It is not just about effort, it is also about the thought process and work ethics... He handles pressure remarkably well. I hope he comes here again in the future to inspire the present generation.         
	Expressing his admiration for both Bindra and Anand, Sourav said it was an honour for him to be sharing the dais with the sporting icons.         
	The left-hander, who has more than 11,000 ODI runs to his credit, stressed on the importance of nurturing talent. Just as we need talent coming in, we also need to show them the right way.                                                                                                                       
